name: Ishikawa Goemon shrine tour -he was jackpot?-
description:
Ishikawa Goemon travels by time machine to a time and place where the secret treasure may exist, in search of the treasure to seal the dragon that brainwashed the shoguns.

This time, I landed in NEO IZUMO in the year 2040.
But all I could see were grasslands and forests, with no humans in sight.
The shrine we visited enshrined koban, which was very valuable in Goemon's time, and would normally be decorated with a statue of a lion dance, but instead there was a statue of NEKONINJAS.

There doesn't seem to be any hidden treasure here.

At a loss, Goemon took a koban and put it in the money box.

A long sentence was inscribed on the statue of NEKONINJAS.
Apparently, somewhere in the lore of history in this world, the facts were falsified and the ninja were told that they were legends that never existed and that they were monsters in the form of cats.


TEZOS NINJAS joined #HENJackpot
